## 3. ARCHITECTURE n8n DISTRIBUEE

### 3.1 Queue Mode avec Redis

Chaque instance n8n est configuree en **queue mode** :

```yaml
# docker-compose.yml (template par repo)
services:
  n8n:
    image: n8nio/n8n:latest
    environment:
      - EXECUTIONS_MODE=queue
      - QUEUE_BULL_REDIS_HOST=redis
      - QUEUE_BULL_REDIS_PORT=6379
      - N8N_CONCURRENCY_PRODUCTION_LIMIT=10
    ports:
      - "5678:5678"

  n8n-worker:
    image: n8nio/n8n:latest
    command: worker --concurrency 10
    environment:
      - EXECUTIONS_MODE=queue
      - QUEUE_BULL_REDIS_HOST=redis
      - QUEUE_BULL_REDIS_PORT=6379

  redis:
    image: redis:7-alpine
    volumes:
      - redis-data:/data
```

### 3.2 Topologie des instances

```
VM Google Cloud (e2-micro, 1 vCPU, 970 MB)
├── n8n-control (mon-ipad)     → Port 5678 (principal)
│   ├── Orchestrator workflow
│   ├── Feedback, Benchmark, Monitoring
│   └── 1 worker local (concurrency=5)
├── Redis (partage)            → Port 6379
└── PostgreSQL (partage)       → Port 5432

Codespace 1 (tests, 2 vCPU, 8 GB)
├── n8n-tests (tests)          → Port 5679
│   ├── Standard, Graph, Quant, Orchestrator workflows
│   └── 2 workers (concurrency=10 chacun)
└── Scripts Python eval

Codespace 2 (data-ingestion, 2 vCPU, 8 GB)
├── n8n-ingest (data-ingestion) → Port 5680
│   ├── Ingestion, Enrichissement workflows
│   └── 1 worker (concurrency=5)
└── Scripts Python ingestion
```

### 3.3 Capacite estimee

| Config | Workers | Concurrency | Capacite max |
|--------|---------|-------------|-------------|
| VM seule (actuel) | 1 | 1 | ~1 exec/s |
| VM + queue mode | 1 | 5 | ~5 exec/s |
| VM + 1 Codespace | 3 | 10 | ~30 exec/s |
| VM + 2 Codespaces | 5 | 10 | ~50 exec/s |
| VM + Cloud Run burst | 5+auto | 10 | ~200 exec/s |

